\begin_layout Standard
By law (2010), the main objectives are 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

maintain price stability and support the economic policy, especially growth,
 employment and social gaps reduction
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The monetary committee has six members, 5 of them appointed by the government
 and 1 is internal.
 The decisions are made by a majority vote, with the governor having a double
 vote.
 The votes are anonymous with collective responsibility - which leads to
 more open discussions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Over the last 20 years, the interest rate in Israeli has been gradually
 decreasing, like in many other countries around the world - together with
 the inflation (increasing technology and Chinese productivity created a
 pressure on it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Phillips curve is so 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

flat
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, because most labor markets are actually global and not national anymore.
 Example: even the X-ray technician at a hospital.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unlike 2008, the COVID-19 crisis was not caused by a financial shock.
 The economy of Israel entered the crisis in a relatively good state (in
 terms of labor market, current account surplus and GDP growth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Response steps taken by the BOI include:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Monetary policy: liquidity on the FXm market, government bonds purchase,
 Shekel liquidity supply
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Credit: reducing capital requirements, loan deferrals, regulatory easings
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Economic advice to the government: fiscal & economic plans, exit strategic
 plan, policy steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unlike normal times, during a crisis keeping the financial stability is
 more important than reaching growth or inflation targets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Institutional investors developed significant exposure to derivatives abroad
 during the last decade, which might be might impose a problem when prices
 go down.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The impact of asset purchase programs was decresaing the yields immediately
 after the announcement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The advantage of the Central Bank, compared to the fiscal authorities -
 is its ability to act much quicker.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During the last 20 years there has been a steady appreciation of the Shekel.
 A strong basic balance continues to support the Shekel, and the private
 equity flows in the Israeli tech sector contribute to it.
\end_layout

